ment": "punctuation", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roger_Mortimer,_4th_Earl_of_March"}
{"title_page": "Luxembourg Commercial Internet eXchange (LU-CIX)", "text_new": "{{Infobox Internet exchange point\n| name         = Luxembourg Commercial Internet eXchange\n| image         = Logo_of_LU-CIX.gif\n| abbreviation = LU-CIX\n| Form         = asbl\n| founded      = 2009\n| members      = 69\n| traffic peaks      = 161,2Gbps\n| location     = 4, rue A. Graham Bell,\n3235 [[Bettembourg]], [[Luxembourg]]\n| website      = [https://www.lu-cix.lu/ www.lu-cix.lu]\n}}\nThe '''Luxembourg Commercial Internet eXchange''' (stylised as '''LU-CIX''') is a carrier and neutral [[internet exchange point]] (IX) located in [[Luxembourg]].\n\n==History==\nLU-CIX was founded in February 2009<ref>[http://www.itnation.lu/news/lancement-de-lu-cix-%E2%80%9Cconnecting-europe-in-one-spot%E2%80%9D/745/ Lancement de LU-CIX] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304041802/http://www.itnation.lu/news/lancement-de-lu-cix-%E2%80%9Cconnecting-europe-in-one-spot%E2%80%9D/745/ |date=2016-03-04 }}, IT nation, 13/10/2009</ref> under the initiative on cross-industry players. \nThese members (listed below) keep running the technical backend requested for LU-CIX to provide its services portfolio.\n\n{{colbegin}}\n*[http://www.bce.lu/ Broadcasting Center Europe]\n*[http://www.cegecom.lu/index.php?id=4 Cegecom]\n*[https://ctie.gouvernement.lu/en.html CTIE]\n*[https://www.datacenter.eu/ Datacenter Luxembourg]\n*[http://www.ebrc.com/ EBRC]\n*[http://www.restena.lu/restena/en/EN-Index.html Fondation Restena] \n*[http://www.gms.lu/ Global Media Systems]\n*[http://www.inexio.net/ Inexio]\n*[http://luxconnect.lu/ LuxConnect]\n*[[:lb:Chambre de commerce Luxembourg|Luxembourg Chamber of Commerce]]\n*[http://www.internet.lu/ Luxembourg Online]\n*[http://www.post.lu/fr/ Post]\n*[http://www.root.lu/ root]\n*[https://securitymadein.lu/ security made in L\u00ebtzebuerg]\n*[http://www.ses.com/ SES Techcom]\n*[http://www.luxnetwork.eu/ Luxnetwork]\n*[http://www.telindus.fr/ Telindus]\n{{colend}}\n\nLU-CIX gathers together national and international telecommunications operators, data centre operators, ISPs and online businesses.<ref>[http://www.lessentiel.lu/fr/economie/story/16291965 Optimiser la transmission des donn\u00e9es], L'essentiel, 13/03/2014</ref>\n\nLU-CIX is a member of Euro-IX (European Internet Exchange Association).\n\n==Mission==\nLU-CIX has been created to support the development of the Internet industry in the heart of Europe and increase the attractiveness of Luxembourg as an ICT Hub in the middle of the so-called \"Golden Ring\".<ref>[http://paperjam.lu/news/lu-cix-deploie-ses-ailes LU-CIX d\u00e9ploie ses ailes], Paperjam, 19/11/2010</ref>\n\nIts philosophy is based on a strong neutrality concept.\n\nTo carry out these missions, LU-CIX:\n- owns and runs the technical IX infrastructure and \n- organises the Luxembourg Internet Days,<ref>[http://www.luxembourg-internet-days.com/ Luxembourg Internet Days]</ref> a yearly event that brings together local & international ICT professionals for conferences, open round tables, trade fair and networking sessions focused on two to three topics to be addressed from a more technical and pragmatic way.<ref>[http://www.soluxions-magazine.com/xaviel-bettel-veut-faire-luxembourg-smart-nation/ Xavier Bettel veut faire de Luxembourg une \"smart nation\"], Soluxions, 19/11/2014</ref>\nIn 2018, the Luxembourg Internet Days took place in Luxembourg city, on November 13 & 14.<ref>[http://www.luxembourg-internet-days.com/ Luxembourg Internet Days 2017]</ref> with more than 1.100 visitors.\nThe 2019 edition of the Luxembourg Internet Days will be held on November 12 & 13 and will focus on Network & Cloud Security and on E-commerce & Digitalisation.\n\nLU-CIX also manages the digital platform [https://datacenters-in-europe.com/ datacenters-in-europe.com], which [https://datacenters-in-europe.com/data-centers/ lists all the data centers] located in [[Luxembourg]].\n\n==Infrastructure==\nLU-CIX is hosted in 8 data centers, [[Point of presence|PoPs]], across the country to facilitate the membership of a majority of Internet related players.\n\nThe traffic peak of LU-CIX is 264,5 Gbps.\n\nIt also leverages strong partnerships with other IX in Europe<ref>[http://www.chronicle.lu/categoriesbusinessitcinternet/item/2636-lu%E2%80%90cix-and-ix-reach-open-up-connectivity-to-major-internet-exchanges LU-CIX and IX Reach open up connectivity to major Internet exchanges], Chronicle, 02/04/2013</ref> ([[European Commercial Internet Exchange|ECIX]] & [[:fr:France IX|FranceIX]]<ref>[http://paperjam.lu/communique/france-ix-et-lu-cix-scellent-leur-partenariat-dans-le-monde-des-points-dechange-internet France IX et LU-CIX scellent leur partenariat dans le monde des points d'\u00e9change Internet], Paperjam, 29/11/2011</ref>).\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Internet exchange points in Luxembourg]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Internet exchange point\n| name         = Luxembourg Commercial Internet eXchange\n| image         = Logo_of_LU-CIX.gif\n| abbreviation = LU-CIX\n| Form         = asbl\n| founded      = 2009\n| members      = 69\n| traffic peaks      = 161,2Gbps\n| location     = 4, rue A. Graham Bell,\n3235 [[Bettembourg]], [[Luxembourg]]\n| website      = [https://www.lu-cix.lu/ www.lu-cix.lu]\n}}\nThe '''Luxembourg Commercial Internet eXchange''' (stylised as '''LU-CIX''') is a carrier and neutral [[internet exchange point]] (IX) located in [[Luxembourg]].\n\n==History==\nLU-CIX was founded in February 2009<ref>[http://www.itnation.lu/news/lancement-de-lu-cix-%E2%80%9Cconnecting-europe-in-one-spot%E2%80%9D/745/ Lancement de LU-CIX] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304041802/http://www.itnation.lu/news/lancement-de-lu-cix-%E2%80%9Cconnecting-europe-in-one-spot%E2%80%9D/745/ |date=2016-03-04 }}, IT nation, 13/10/2009</ref> under the initiative on cross-industry players. \nThese members (listed below) keep running the technical backend requested for LU-CIX to provide its services portfolio.\n\n{{colbegin}}\n*[http://www.bce.lu/ Broadcasting Center Europe]\n*[http://www.cegecom.lu/index.php?id=4 Cegecom]\n*[https://ctie.gouvernement.lu/en.html CTIE]\n*[https://www.datacenter.eu/ Datacenter Luxembourg]\n*[http://www.ebrc.com/ EBRC]\n*[http://www.restena.lu/restena/en/EN-Index.html Fondation Restena] \n*[http://www.gms.lu/ Global Media Systems]\n*[http://www.inexio.net/ Inexio]\n*[http://luxconnect.lu/ LuxConnect]\n*[[:lb:Chambre de commerce Luxembourg|Luxembourg Chamber of Commerce]]\n*[http://www.internet.lu/ Luxembourg Online]\n*[http://www.post.lu/fr/ Post]\n*[http://www.root.lu/ root]\n*[https://securitymadein.lu/ security made in L\u00ebtzebuerg]\n*[http://www.ses.com/ SES Techcom]\n*[http://www.luxnetwork.eu/ Luxnetwork]\n*[http://www.telindus.fr/ Telindus]\n{{colend}}\n\nLU-CIX gathers together national and international telecommunications operators, data centre operators, ISPs and online businesses.<ref>[http://www.lessentiel.lu/fr/economie/story/16291965 Optimiser la transmission des donn\u00e9es], L'essentiel, 13/03/2014</ref>\n\nLU-CIX is a member of Euro-IX (European Internet Exchange Association).\n\n==Mission==\nLU-CIX has been created to support the development of the Internet industry in the heart of Europe and increase the attractiveness of Luxembourg as an ICT Hub in the middle of the so-called \"Golden Ring\".<ref>[http://paperjam.lu/news/lu-cix-deploie-ses-ailes LU-CIX d\u00e9ploie ses ailes], Paperjam, 19/11/2010</ref>\n\nIts philosophy is based on a strong neutrality concept.\n\nTo carry out these missions, LU-CIX:\n- owns and runs the technical IX infrastructure and \n- organises the Luxembourg Internet Days,<ref>[http://www.luxembourg-internet-days.com/ Luxembourg Internet Days]</ref> a yearly event that brings together local & international ICT professionals for conferences, open round tables, trade fair and networking sessions focused on two to three topics to be addressed from a more technical and pragmatic way.<ref>[http://www.soluxions-magazine.com/xaviel-bettel-veut-faire-luxembourg-smart-nation/ Xavier Bettel veut faire de Luxembourg une \"smart nation\"], Soluxions, 19/11/2014</ref>\nIn 2018, the Luxembourg Internet Days took place in Luxembourg city, on November 13 & 14.<ref>[http://www.luxembourg-internet-days.com/ Luxembourg Internet Days 2017]</ref> with more than 1.100 visitors.\nThe 2019 edition of the Luxembourg Internet Days will be held on November 12 & 13 and will focus on Network & Cloud Security and on E-commerce & Digitalisation.\n\nLU-CIX also manages the digital platform [https://datacenters-in-europe.com/ datacenters-in-europe.com], which [https://datacenters-in-europe.com/data-centers/ lists all the data centers] located in [[Luxembourg]].\n\n==Infrastructure==\nLU-CIX is hosted in 8 data centers, [[Point of presence|PoPs]], across the country to facilitate the membership of a majority of Internet related players.\n\nThe traffic peak of LU-CIX is 157,8 Gbps.\n\nIt also leverages strong partnerships with other IX in Europe<ref>[http://www.chronicle.lu/categoriesbusinessitcinternet/item/2636-lu%E2%80%90cix-and-ix-reach-open-up-connectivity-to-major-internet-exchanges LU-CIX and IX Reach open up connectivity to major Internet exchanges], Chronicle, 02/04/2013</ref> ([[European Commercial Internet Exchange|ECIX]] & [[:fr:France IX|FranceIX]]<ref>[http://paperjam.lu/communique/france-ix-et-lu-cix-scellent-leur-partenariat-dans-le-monde-des-points-dechange-internet France IX et LU-CIX scellent leur partenariat dans le monde des points d'\u00e9change Internet], Paperjam, 29/11/2011</ref>).\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Internet exchange points in Luxembourg]]\n", "name_user": "Lola2012", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eInfrastructure", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luxembourg_Commercial_Internet_eXchange_(LU-CIX)"}
{"title_page": "Fundus", "text_new": "{{wiktionary|fundus}}\n'''''Fundus''''' (Latin for \"bottom\") is an anatomical term referring to that part of a concavity in any organ, which is at the far end from its opening. It may refer to:\n==Anatomy==\n* [[Fundus (brain)]], the deepest part of any [[sulcus]] of the [[cerebral cortex]]\n* [[Fundus (eye)]], the interior surface of the eye, opposite the lens, and including the retina, optic disc, macula and fovea, and posterior pole\n** [[Fundus camera]], equipment for photographing the interior of the eye\n** [[Fundus photography]]\n* [[Fundus (stomach)]], the portion of the stomach which bulges up past the point of entry of the esophagus\n* [[Fundus (uterus)]], the top portion, opposite from the cervix\n* [[Fundus of gallbladder]], the portion of the gallbladder which lies the farthest from the cystic duct\n* [[Fundus of the urinary bladder]]\n\n==Other uses==\n* [[Fundus (seabed)]], the seabed in a tidal river below low water mark\n\n{{disambiguation}}\n", "text_old": "{{wiktionary|fundus}}\n'''''Fundus''''' (Latin for \"bottom\") is an anatomical term referring to that part of a concavity in any organ, which is at the far end from its opening. It may refer to:\n==Anatomy==\n* [[Fundus (brain)]], the deepest part of any sulcus of the cerebral cortex\n* [[Fundus (eye)]], the interior surface of the eye, opposite the lens, and including the retina, optic disc, macula and fovea, and posterior pole\n** [[Fundus camera]], equipment for photographing the interior of the eye\n** [[Fundus photography]]\n* [[Fundus (stomach)]], the portion of the stomach which bulges up past the point of entry of the esophagus\n* [[Fundus (uterus)]], the top portion, opposite from the cervix\n* [[Fundus of gallbladder]], the portion of the gallbladder which lies the farthest from the cystic duct\n* [[Fundus of the urinary bladder]]\n\n==Other uses==\n* [[Fundus (seabed)]], the seabed in a tidal river below low water mark\n\n{{disambiguation}}\n",